Robbie McNamara broke eight ribs and cracked six vertebrae in a fall at Wexford . 
  McNamara says he is feeling 'great and optimistic' as he continues to recover from serious injuries . 
  The jockey was due to partner Lord Windermere in the Grand National at Aintree . 
  He has no feeling in his legs but was able to leave his bed for the first time . 
 